(GradFix Work Orders - Design Gist) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Main conclusion) Tj T*
(Work Orders should be a separate operational subsystem, not just a PDF field on reports.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(A report is the citizen-facing issue record.) Tj T*
(A work order is an operational instruction sent to one responsible entity to perform work.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Recommended domain rule) Tj T*
(One report can generate zero, one, or many work orders.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Why this matters) Tj T*
(Real city problems often involve multiple services. For example, one traffic issue may need) Tj T*
(road repair,) Tj T*
(temporary signs, and later repainting. A single reports.assigned_entity_id field is not) Tj T*
(enough.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Core actors) Tj T*
(- Citizen: creates report, receives updates, may confirm/rate resolution.) Tj T*
(- Reviewer: accepts reports and verifies completed work.) Tj T*
(- Conductor: creates, sends, retries, reassigns, cancels, and completes work orders.) Tj T*
(- Tenant Admin: can override and manage all tenant work-order actions.) Tj T*
(- Community Manager: can view/communicate, but should not normally create or cancel work) Tj T*
(orders.) Tj T*
(- Responsible Entity: receives the work order and performs the work.) Tj T*
(- System: generates PDFs, sends emails, records delivery failures, and logs events.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Recommended entities) Tj T*
(- work_orders) Tj T*
(- work_order_documents) Tj T*
(- work_order_deliveries) Tj T*
(- work_order_events) Tj T*
(- optional work_order_photos) Tj T*
(- optional work_order_items) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Recommended relationships) Tj T*
(- reports 1:N work_orders) Tj T*
(- responsible_entities 1:N work_orders) Tj T*
(- work_orders 1:N work_order_documents) Tj T*
(- work_orders 1:N work_order_deliveries) Tj T*
(- work_orders 1:N work_order_events) Tj T*
(- report_photos N:M work_orders, if staff can choose which photos are included) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Recommended work order states) Tj T*
(- draft) Tj T*
(- ready_to_send) Tj T*
(- sending) Tj T*
(- sent) Tj T*
(- delivery_failed) Tj T*
(- acknowledged) Tj T*
(- in_progress) Tj T*
(- completed) Tj T*
(- verified) Tj T*
(- cancelled) Tj T*
(- superseded) Tj T*
(- closed) Tj T*
() Tj T*
ET
endstream
