(- regenerate after send) Tj T*
(- supersede work order) Tj T*
(- reopen completed work) Tj T*
(- close report while work is active) Tj T*
(- merge duplicate reports when work orders exist) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Email flow) Tj T*
(1. Staff reviews work order.) Tj T*
(2. PDF snapshot is generated.) Tj T*
(3. Delivery record is created as queued.) Tj T*
(4. Email job sends PDF or secure PDF link.) Tj T*
(5. Delivery becomes sent or delivery_failed.) Tj T*
(6. Failed delivery can be retried.) Tj T*
(7. Every attempt is audited.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(PDF flow) Tj T*
(1. Snapshot report details, location, priority, category, selected photos, and responsible) Tj T*
(entity.) Tj T*
(2. Generate immutable PDF document.) Tj T*
(3. Store file key, checksum, generated_by, generated_at.) Tj T*
(4. Sending uses the current PDF version.) Tj T*
(5. Regeneration after send creates a new version.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Security requirements) Tj T*
(- Every work order must have tenant_id.) Tj T*
(- Every query must filter by tenant_id.) Tj T*
(- Tenant-bound users must not access another tenant's work orders.) Tj T*
(- PDFs should be private or use signed URLs.) Tj T*
(- Reporter PII should not be included by default.) Tj T*
(- Email templates must escape user-generated content.) Tj T*
(- All send/regenerate/cancel actions must be audited.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Three architecture options) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Option 1: Add PDF fields directly to reports) Tj T*
(Pros: fastest, easiest demo.) Tj T*
(Cons: cannot support multiple services, retries, document versions, real audit, or proper) Tj T*
(cancellation.) Tj T*
(Verdict: not recommended.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Option 2: One work_order per report) Tj T*
(Pros: cleaner than report fields, separate status.) Tj T*
(Cons: still assumes one service per report and will need redesign later.) Tj T*
(Verdict: better, but too limiting.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Option 3: Full Work Order subsystem) Tj T*
(Pros: supports multiple services, multiple work orders, retries, immutable PDFs, audit,) Tj T*
(reassignment, and future contractor portal.) Tj T*
(Cons: more design and implementation work.) Tj T*
(Verdict: recommended.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Best recommendation) Tj T*
(Use Option 3.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Build Work Orders as first-class operational records with their own lifecycle, documents,) Tj T*
(deliveries,) Tj T*
(and audit events. Keep the UI simple at first, but do not compromise the database/domain) Tj T*
ET
endstream
